Kevin receives points for substrings that start with a vowel.

Stuart receives points for substrings that start with a consonant.

Task

Complete the function minion_game.

The function should print one of the following:

Kevin <score>

or

Stuart <score>

or

Draw

if both players have the same score.


> SOLUTION:

def minion_game(string):
    
    vowels={'A','E','I','O','U'}
    Stuart = 0
    Kevin = 0
    n = len(string)
    
    for i in range(n):
        if string[i] in vowels:
            Kevin += n-i
            
        else:
            Stuart += n-i
            
    if Kevin > Stuart:
        print("Kevin",Kevin)
    elif Stuart > Kevin:
        print("Stuart",Stuart)
    else:
        print("Draw")


if __name__ == '__main__':
    s = input()
    minion_game(s)
